# BlazeSwap
#### The first open-source fully decentralized exchange on the Flare Network.
Brought to you by the A-FTSO provider.
[![Explore Flare's ecosystem and unlock rewards by staking, supplying, and lending with BlazeSwap](https://blazeswap.xyz/flare-carnival-2025/1200x400.jpg)](https://fair.flare.network/?utm_source=blazeswap&utm_medium=eco_partners&utm_campaign=fair)
## Features
Trade any token at the best rates. Provide liquidity to earn commissions and rewards.
Fast trade settlement, immediate trade finality and extremely low transaction fees.
Vote for the FTSO provider delegation and claim your rewards. The process is controlled by smart contracts and mimics the Flare distribution, no more missed rewards.
Use F-Assets bridged tokens with confidence, the incentives are distributed to the liquidity providers pro-rata.
Liquidity providers will be able to claim the airdropped tokens on Flare, without fear of losing their 85% airdrop.
Use the API for advanced interactions, automated trading, flash swaps and price oracles.
## FAQ
All 
Fees 
Flare 
FTSO 
Liquidity 
Rewards 
Security 
Tokens 
Wallets 
Has the platform been audited? 
Yes, the platform has been audited by the specialized security firm Omniscia. No major issues have been found, and all minor issues have been addressed. The report is available [here](https://omniscia.io/reports/blazeswap-decentralized-exchange/).
Is there a bug bounty program? 
Yes, we have an active bug bounty program to reward users that find severe issues in the smart contracts of the DEX. For more details look at the dedicated [page](https://blazeswap.xyz/bounty).
Will I lose my FTSO rewards if I put liquidity into the BlazeSwap pools? 
No, you can safely put your FLR/SGB/CFLR/C2FLR into a liquidity pool and claim your periodic rewards. The timings, the amounts and the reward expirations are identical to what you've been used to, the only difference is the interface to claim them. We don't select the FTSO providers on your behalf, the liquidity providers can vote for their preferred provider.
Will I lose the Flare Airdrop (FlareDrops) if I put liquidity into the BlazeSwap pools? 
No, as for the FTSO rewards, on the Flare and Coston2 networks you can claim your monthly FlareDrop. The systems uses the same 3 snapshots to distribute the airdrop to the liquidity providers, so the timings, the amounts and the expiration match what you'd expect.
What tokens can I trade? 
You can trade any ERC-20 compliant fungible token. There is a curated list of known ERC-20 tokens that is pre-defined, but you are free to add any new token. Non Fungible Tokens (NFTs) are not supported.
How can I get some free tokens to play with the DEX? 
On Coston/Coston2 we have deployed a few test tokens you can play with. You can either exchange your CFLR/C2FLR for one of them, or you can directly mint them [here](https://app.blazeswap.xyz/test/mint).
Is there a BlazeSwap token or NFTs? 
No, we don't think the platform needs a governance or a utility token and we don't want to make money by issuing a (useless) token. The LP tokens are enough to vote for providers delegation and anyone can add new tokens and pair, so there is no need for a BlazeSwap token or NFT.
Will you add farming pools? 
No, since there isn't a BlazeSwap token there won't be farming pools. Liquidity providers will earn tokens from the trading fees, trading is the main purpose of a DEX and trading fees are the main source of revenue. We don't want to attract liquidity by deceiving people into thinking that they will earn a (useless) token.
What are the trader and liquidity provider fees? 
As a trader, every swap will have a fixed 0.3% fee. As a liquidity provider you will get your share of such 0.3% fee, pro-rata.
What are the platform fees? 
The platform currently has no fees. Any fee activation will be announced at least 15 days in advance. The allowed fee percentages are hard-coded in the smart contracts and we cannot increase them, so there is no risk you'll get charged more than expected. Our swap fee, when enabled, will be 0.05%, that has to be substracted to what the liquidity providers will get. So for the trader it'll remain 0.3%, while the liquidity providers will get their 0.25% pro-rata. Other fees might be enabled (and disabled as well) on the Flare generated rewards, always within the hard-coded limits.
As a liquidity provider may I incur in an "impermanent loss"? What is it? 
Yes, the impermanent (sometimes called divergence) loss is the effect caused by the difference of the pool rate between the time you provided liquidity and the time you withdrew it.

chunk:
It's called impermanent because it can be nullified if the price returns to the same value as when the liquidity was added, and the loss is only realized when the liquidity is removed. The actual return for liquidity providers is a balance between the impermanent loss caused by the price differential and the accumulated trading fees.
What wallet do you support? 
Any web3-enabled wallet/browser and any wallet supporting WalletConnect v1 should work with BlazeSwap. We've successfully tested the MetaMask and Rabby browser extensions on desktop, and Bifrost/D'CENT apps on mobile. We don't recommend MetaMask Mobile because of a few unsolved bugs that we have encountered. 
Supported browsers: Brave, Chrome/Chromium, Edge, Firefox.
Why does the user interface stop working correctly after a few transaction with MetaMask? Is your app broken? 
While we cannot exclude bugs in our frontend app, you are probably hitting the rate limit of the public Flare RPC endpoint. Unfortunately MetaMask does a lot of RPC calls for each transaction. We suggest to either switch to a different wallet or to use a node with a higher limit. You can get a subscription, with a free plan including 1000 requests/day, from the Flare [API Portal](https://api-portal.flare.network/).
Why I don't see my pools with custom tokens, or rewards from pools where I removed my liquidity, when using the in-app Bifrost browser? 
Bifrost is currently running the in-app browser in incognito mode. This means that all settings, including the added custom tokens and the list of pools from which you removed your entire liquidity, are wiped when the page is closed. This behavior might change in future, but in the meantime we've added shortcuts to re-add the token/pool from the Pools and Rewards pages.
Is it possible to do swaps via API, without the web interface? 
It's possible to directly call the smart contracts, the workflow is very similar to Uniswap V2. We published a [npm package](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@blazeswap/contracts) with the contracts' interfaces and their artifacts that you can use in plain JavaScript or in TypeScript with TypeChain. We'll likely provide a SDK in the future. Get in touch with us if you are a wallet provider and would like to integrate swaps in your app.
Why don't you have a cookie banner on your website? Are you not GDPR compliant? 
We haven't a cookie banner because we are not setting any cookie. We are strongly against trackers and advertisement.

# Bug Bounty Program
Effective date: 27 October 2022
## Overview
This bug bounty program is focused on the BlazeSwap smart contracts, and in particular on preventing:
  * Theft of user funds (critical)
  * Permanent freeze of user funds (critical)
  * Theft of user rewards (high)
  * Permanent freeze of user rewards (high)
  * Delegation activity disruption (high)
  * Rewards claiming disruption (high)
  * Denial of Service by putting contracts in unforeseeable state (high)


Other reports of incorrect behaviors will be considered by the team, but the issuance of a reward (if any) will be at its own discretionality.
The website and the DEX web interface are excluded from the bug bounty program.
## Rewards
Rewards will be provided for critical & high vulnerabilities only, and distributed according to the impact of the issue and the quality of the report.
The submission of a PoC and/or a suggestion for a fix may entail for a higher amount within the reward range, compared to the same report without them.
The payouts are denominated in SGB and will be provided on the Songbird network. The kind of vulnerability and the exact reward amount will be defined at the sole discretion of the BlazeSwap team.
  * Critical: from 500,000 SGB to 1,000,000 SGB
  * High: from 25,000 SGB to 500,000 SGB


For valid reports submitted before 15 June 2023 the upper bound of the reward ranges is increased by 50%:
  * Critical: up to 1,500,000 SGB
  * High: up to 750,000 SGB


## Scope
The latest version of all smart contracts of BlazeSwap can be found at <https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts>.
However, only the following contracts (including parent contracts and included libraries) are in the scope of this bug bounty program:
  * [BlazeSwapManager](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapManager.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapExecutorManager](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapExecutorManager.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapFactory](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapFactory.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapPair](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapPair.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapRewards](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapRewards.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapRewardsPlugin](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapRewardsPlugin.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapDelegation](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapDelegation.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapDelegationPlugin](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapDelegationPlugin.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapFtsoReward](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapFtsoReward.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapFtsoRewardPlugin](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapFtsoRewardPlugin.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapAirdrop](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapAirdrop.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapAirdropPlugin](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapAirdropPlugin.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapRewardManager](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/core/BlazeSwapRewardManager.sol)
  * [BlazeSwapRouter](https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/blob/main/contracts/periphery/BlazeSwapRouter.sol)


## Rules
All known issues highlighted in the following audit report are considered to be out of scope: <https://omniscia.io/reports/blazeswap-decentralized-exchange>
The following vulnerabilities are excluded from the rewards for this bug bounty program:
  * Vulnerabilities previouly reported by other users
  * Issues already listed on GitHub: <https://github.com/blazeswap/contracts/issues>
  * Bugs that the reporter has already exploited themselves, leading to damage
  * Attacks requiring access to leaked keys/credentials
  * Attacks that rely on social engineering
  * Issues caused by non compliant ERC-20 tokens
  * Issues deriving from unforeseeable and/or unexpected problems in called Flare's smart contracts
  * Issues caused by an incorrect/incomplete deployment and/or initialization of the smart contracts (in particular, all plugins are expected to be available from the beginning, with the sole exception of the BlazeSwapFlareAssetRewardPlugin)
  * Possible attacks deriving from a future implementation of the BlazeSwapFlareAssetRewardPlugin
  * Basic economic governance attacks (e.g. 51% attack)
  * Lack of liquidity
  * Best practice critiques
  * Sybil attacks

The following activities are prohibited by this bug bounty program:
  * Any testing with mainnet (Flare & Songbird) and public testnets (Coston & Coston2) contracts; all testing should be done on private testnets
  * Any denial of service attacks
  * Public disclosure of an unpatched vulnerability in an embargoed bounty


## Submission
The detailed report of the discovered vulnerability, and the Songbird address to receive the bounty, must be sent via email to the following email address:  Click to show email 
The team has 15 days to verify the claim and/or ask for additional documentation. No public disclosure can happen during this timeframe.
If the vulnerability is not considered valid by the team, the reporter is free to disclose it. Otherwise, the embargo remains in effect until a proper fix is implemented by the team.
If it's the first report for such vulnerability the reporter is entitled to receive the reward.
## Changes
The terms of this bug bounty program can be changed at any time. The program can also be terminated. However, reports submitted before the changes are subject to the previous terms.
